This paper deals with covert communication, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and security (cs.CR). The use of noise uncertainty in evaluating covertness also involves signal processing (cs.MM) and networking (cs.NI) techniques. Additionally, the development of new metrics for measuring covertness can be seen as a contribution to the field of social and information sciences (cs.SI).
